## Organizing Your Workspace

### 31. Starring Important Channels or Messages

**To star a channel:**
1. Open the channel
2. Click the **star icon** below the channel name
3. The channel moves to the **Starred** section at the top of your sidebar

**To star a message:**
1. Hover over a message
2. Click the **three dots** (More actions)
3. Select **Star message**
4. Find all starred messages by clicking the **star icon** in the top-right corner

### 32. Pinning Important Messages in a Channel

1. Hover over the message you want to pin
2. Click the **three dots** (More actions)
3. Select **Pin to channel**
4. Click **Yes, pin this message**
5. A confirmation appears at the top of the channel

**To view pinned messages:**
1. Click the channel name at the top
2. Click the **Pinned** tab
3. All pinned items appear in chronological order

**To unpin a message:**
1. Access the pinned items list
2. Hover over the pinned message
3. Click the **X (Remove)** button
4. Confirm by clicking **Yes, remove this pinned item**

### 33. Using the All Unreads View

1. Click **All Unreads** at the top of your left sidebar
2. All unread messages from all channels appear in one consolidated view
3. Messages are sorted by:
   - Most recent (default)
   - Scientific (Slack predicts most important)
   - Alphabetical
4. Click the dropdown to change sorting
5. Read through messages
6. Press **Esc** to mark the current channel as read

### 34. Marking All Messages as Read

**To mark one channel as read:**
1. Open the channel
2. Press **Esc** on your keyboard
3. All messages are marked as read

**To mark ALL channels as read:**
1. Press **Shift + Esc** on your keyboard
2. Every message across all channels is marked as read
3. Use this carefully – you can't undo this action

