## Keyboard Shortcuts

### 56. Using Quick Switcher

1. Press **Cmd + K** (Mac) or **Ctrl + K** (Windows/Linux)
2. The Quick Switcher opens
3. Start typing a channel name, person's name, or workspace name
4. Use arrow keys to navigate suggestions
5. Press **Enter** to switch to that location

**Shortcut variations:**
- Press **Cmd/Ctrl + T** to open Quick Switcher directly to channels
- Type **#** before your search to see only public channels
- Type **@** before your search to see only direct messages

### 57. Navigating Between Channels with Keyboard

- **Alt + ↑** (Windows) or **Option + ↑** (Mac): Move to previous channel
- **Alt + ↓** (Windows) or **Option + ↓** (Mac): Move to next channel
- **Cmd/Ctrl + Shift + A**: Open All Unreads view
- **Cmd/Ctrl + Shift + S**: Open Starred Items
- **Cmd/Ctrl + .**: Open the right sidebar (threads/details)

### 58. Message Editing Shortcuts

- **↑**: Edit your last message
- **Esc**: Mark channel as read
- **Shift + Esc**: Mark all messages in all channels as read
- **Cmd/Ctrl + B**: Make text bold
- **Cmd/Ctrl + I**: Make text italic
- **Cmd/Ctrl + Shift + X**: Strikethrough text
- **Shift + Enter**: Create new line without sending

### 59. Viewing All Keyboard Shortcuts

1. Press **Cmd + /** (Mac) or **Ctrl + /** (Windows/Linux)
2. A complete list of shortcuts appears
3. Browse by category
4. Click **X** or press **Esc** to close

