## Troubleshooting and Getting Help

### 69. Searching the Slack Help Center

1. Go to https://slack.com/help
2. Use the search bar to type your question
3. Review suggested articles
4. Click on an article to read the full instructions
5. Scroll through related articles at the bottom

### 70. Contacting Your Workspace Admin

1. Click your **workspace name** in the top-left
2. Look for admin names (they may have "Admin" or "Owner" in their title)
3. Send them a direct message:
   - Click the **+** next to Direct Messages
   - Type the admin's name
   - Press **Enter** and explain your issue

### 71. Reporting a Problem with Slack

1. Click **Help** in the bottom-left corner
2. Select **Contact Us** or **Report a Problem**
3. Choose your issue category
4. Describe the problem in detail
5. Click **Submit**
6. Slack support will respond via email

### 72. Viewing Your Activity Log

1. Click your **profile picture** in the top-right
2. Select **Profile & account**
3. Click **View Account Settings**
4. Select **Access logs** in the left menu
5. Review all your sign-in activity and locations
6. If you see suspicious activity, click **Sign out all other sessions**

